{#- TL;DR (body) — #methodology-tldr-body = speakable. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="methodology-tldr" style="padding-top:8px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">How a TechBrot engagement works.</h2>
    <div class="tldr-prose"><p id="methodology-tldr-body">Every TechBrot engagement follows five consistent phases. <strong>1) Discovery</strong> &mdash; a free 30-minute call with a Certified ProAdvisor, with an honest assessment of fit. <strong>2) Written fixed-fee scope</strong> &mdash; within 3 business days you receive exactly what will be done, by when, and for what fixed fee; no hourly billing. <strong>3) Onboarding</strong> &mdash; a named ProAdvisor is assigned and you grant accountant-user access to your own QuickBooks file. <strong>4) Delivery</strong> &mdash; the work happens inside your file, audit trail visible to you, on a consistent rhythm. <strong>5) CPA-ready handoff</strong> &mdash; books stay CPA-ready throughout, with year-end files delivered to your CPA at no extra cost. The methodology is identical across bookkeeping, QuickBooks, payroll, sales tax, and fractional CFO &mdash; consistency is what makes engaging TechBrot predictable rather than a gamble.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

