{#- PROCESS — the five phases → process-grid (baseline h3s: phase names). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="methodology-process" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The five phases</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">From first contact to ongoing delivery.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:68ch;">Each phase has a defined output &mdash; so you always know where the engagement stands.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for ph in phases %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">STEP {{ loop.index }}</div><h3>{{ ph.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ ph.body | safe }}</p><p style="margin-top:8px;"><strong>Output:</strong> {{ ph.out | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- WHY — prose. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="methodology-why">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Why it&rsquo;s built this way</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Predictability is the point.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <blockquote class="pull-quote"><p>The process is the product. Consistency is what makes engaging TechBrot predictable rather than a gamble.</p></blockquote>
      <p>Most small businesses have a bad accounting story &mdash; the bookkeeper who vanished, the surprise invoice, the books that turned out to be wrong at tax time, the firm that rotated them through three account managers in a year. Those failures almost always trace back to the same root cause: <strong>no defined process</strong>.</p>
      <p>TechBrot&rsquo;s methodology exists to remove that risk. A written scope means you&rsquo;re never surprised by cost or deliverables. A named ProAdvisor means you&rsquo;re never re-explaining your business or wondering who&rsquo;s responsible. Working inside your own file means you never lose control of your data. CPA-ready books mean tax season is never a fire drill.</p>
      <p>None of this is exotic &mdash; it&rsquo;s simply what an operationally mature firm does. The difference is that TechBrot makes it explicit and applies it the same way to every engagement, every time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

